text: Andrew Neu (June 20, 1873 - July 16, 1959) was an American gymnast. He competed in three events at the 1904 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1873 births Category:1959 deaths Category:American male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the United States Category:Gymnasts at the 1904 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from St. Louis
